I was concerned by the javadocs on the getOption method which says:
@return  The value of the socket option. A value of {@code null} may be a valid value for some socket options.

Rereading the Javadocs for the various socket options, it should be clear from their javadocs that the ones used are not returning null. I've amended the logic accordingly (but added an assertion instead)

